    </td>
    <td width="372" valign="top" align="left"><strong><font face="Verdana">Wus Fighting Gauntlets
    </font></strong><br>
    <font face="verdana" color="White" size="2"><b>
    
		Magical Item<br>
	
    </b></font></td>
    <td width="121" height="1" valign="top" align="center"><p align="center"><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Magic Armour Items</b></font><br>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td></tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3" align="left">
		
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			

					AC:&nbsp; </font><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white">4&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">Weight:&nbsp; </font><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white">0.1&nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
	
		
		 
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td></tr>
  <tr>
    <td width colspan="3" align="left" rowspan="7" valign="top"><font face="Verdana">
    Simply put these are about the best monk gloves in the game for the first 30 or so levels.  They are the product of Tailoring Heady Kiola's Lightstones Viscous Mana and such.  They throw the same light as a Greater Lightstone when worn or in the top level of inventory
		</font></td>
    
  
	 	
  </tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td></tr>
  
</table><br>
